  "label": "The Saltwrit Grotto",
  "description": "The Saltwrit Grotto forms a low, twisting chamber cut through black limestone, its walls veined with pale mineral bands that read like old script in torchlight. Brine weeps steadily from hairline fractures, leaving crusted shelves of salt that blunt sound and preserve refuse to a dry brittleness. A scatter of collapsed stone markers and half-buried cairn rings indicates prior surveying under some chartered authority now lapsed. The air carries a persistent metallic tang, and the floor falls in shallow steps toward a lightless sump where water stands unmoving.",
